com.kontakt.sdk.android.ble.manager

Interface ProximityManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ProximityManagerImpl

    public interface ProximityManager
    Proximity Manager is an entry point for all operations connected with ranging and monitoring BLE devices (iBeacons, Eddystones and Kontakt.io Beacon Pro secure profiles).

    • Method Detail

      • connect

        void connect(OnServiceReadyListener onServiceReadyListener)
        Connects to backing ProximityService. This needs to be done before first calling startScanning().
        Parameters:
        onServiceReadyListener - Listener used to specify if ProximityManager has successfully connected to backing service. This means that all necessary Android permissions have been granted and ProximityManager is ready to start scanning.

      • disconnect

        void disconnect()
        Finishes scanning and disconnects from backing service. Calling connect(OnServiceReadyListener) is required if scanning should be started again.

      • startScanning

        void startScanning()
        Starts scanning for Kontakt.io devices.

      • stopScanning

        void stopScanning()
        Stops scanning. Does not disconnect from backing service. Call disconnect() to disconnect.

      • restartScanning

        void restartScanning()
        Stops scanning, applies latest configuration and restarts scanning.

      • isConnected

        boolean isConnected()
        Returns:
        True if ProximityManager is connected to backing service and ready to scan.

      • isScanning

        boolean isScanning()
        Returns:
        True if scanning is currently in progress.
